Total=80    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont">    Well, after my fellowship getting it&#39;s butt kicked with my last Balrog deck (&quot;See Balroggin&#39; In The Free World&quot;), I decided to beef up the fellowship side a bit.  Gandalf is awesome.  He can become power 12 without any support if you can spot all the other Free Peoples cultures and he has Glamdring.  When he is set up like this, he usually can fight without need of support.  The other characters can be quite powerful as well.  I put in duplicates of many useful cards to allow them to get a better chance of being drawn, and the Gandalf events (Staff Asunder) can take care of many of the other more powerful minions, such as the Balrog (watch out for those final Cries!), Lurtz with his sword, The Witch King, The Cave Troll, and maybe Morgul Hunters if you have a large fellowship.  You can cancel many of the skirmishes as well with Gandalf&#39;s Staff, and make them -3 with Servant of The Secret Fire.  Be sure to win the bid so you can play the Pony, as Aragorn is vital to this deck.  Nazgul are probably the anti for this deck, for Aragorn and Borimir with Flaming Brands and their respective weapons can usually take them out without support.  This deck is kind of weak in that you can&#39;t get rid of any shadow conditions, and since every card in the deck is useful (if not vital), it will have a tough time going against discard decks.  I labeled this deck as an advanced deck just because of the large number of rares in it, not for how good it is, so please review accordingly.  <br>
<br>
   The shadow side focuses on The Balrog.  With his whip, sword, and Final Cry, The balrog can take out pretty much anyone, except maybe for an insanely buffed-up Gimili with Flurry of Blows and 4 Endurance of The Dwarves to keep from getting wounded 6 times from Final Cry.  The Cave Troll can get pretty powerful as well.  Use Foul Things to keep playing him, and use runners and Goblin Armories to add to the Twilight.  Just play whatever minions you can and the shadow side does a good job of slowing the opponent down, giving him wounds and making him stop and heal at sancuaries. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/lotr/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=22535"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=22535" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/lotr/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
